## What I do

I embed with leadership to find where product alignment breaks, so we can pull everything that is product together, and make sure product strategy, positioning and go-to-market is moving in the same direction. I also mentor product managers, while working shoulder to shoulder with engineering, revenue and creative teams.

## What I’m good at

- Product strategy for companies between product-market fit and scale
- Market segmentation and ICP definition — figuring out who to serve and who to say no to
- Aligning product, sales, and engineering teams around shared priorities
- Building value-based roadmaps that connect product decisions to business outcomes
- Positioning and messaging — translating what a product does into a story that sells
- Enterprise readiness assessment — what needs to be true before selling to large organisations
- UX direction and product marketing alignment

## Who I work with

Startups & scale-ups ready to align product, engineering and commercial for the next phase of growth. 
Leadership teams navigating a growth transition.
Companies building a product function for the first time.
Companies thinking about ROI.

## How I work

I start with a Product Clarity Sprint: I talk to the key people, look at the product, positioning, market, process and team alignment, surface where the problems are and what to do about them. This typically takes 2–3 days and results in a clear picture of what’s misaligned, what to prioritise, and concrete next steps.

Most clients use this as a starting point. From there, it often evolves into an embedded engagement — 2–5 days per week — where I work alongside the team as a strategic partner, not a consultant writing reports from the outside.

I automate what can be automated and keep the human-in-the-loop for what matters. I use AI extensively for research, analysis, and product operations, which means I can cover more ground in less time than a traditional product hire.

